    • Anthony S.
      Elite 25
      San Francisco, CA
      12 Coffee reviews
      Aug 26, 2022

      Note this is focused solely on the coffee, not the service or building/atmosphere as those were great. I was really hoping to like this place and consider it as a replacement for Starbucks for my cold and nitro brews but unfortunately, it's just too "unique" for me. By that I mean their coffee I tried (referenced above) does not taste like regular coffee by any means, it's more floral tasting and it's just not my cup of tea. I was definitely super disappointed, after waiting in line to get this odd tasting cold brew, so I can say without any uncertainty that I'm not coming back. So unless you're into unique coffee profiles, this is not the place for you. If I had to compare this to anything, think of it as a if you like Bud Light but then you are coerced into trying an IPA. The coffee served here is the IPA.

    • Kelsey B.
      Denver, CO
      17 Coffee reviews
      Sep 11, 2022

      This place is unique, and had a fresh take on a coffee shop. I went with a group who are all coffee drinkers, and although I am not a coffee drinker I felt they had a lot of great options for other beverages to try that were creative.

      As a non-coffee drinker I hate going to coffee shops with very little options, so Blueprint definitely gets 5 stars from me from that perspective. I ordered a chai soda, which I have never heard of before and I was pleasantly surprised! It was a chai latte with some sort of carbonation, not sure I would order it again but I really enjoyed having the option to try something new.

      Their food menu was pretty extensive for a coffee shop which was also nice. I had been traveling all day and hadn't eaten since 7am that morning so when I visited around 4pm I was starving. I ended up ordering the yogurt parfait, which I expected to be high quality based on the price but I was pretty disappointed. It ended up being a small portion size of yogurt, with granola and a little fruit on the side. The description on the menu made it seem like it included more in it, but it was definitely something I could have gotten at a grocery store for cheaper and a larger portion.

      Lots of seating available, and they had a great patio with seating in the back too. Service was friendly, although a little slow.

      I would definitely go back, but I would order something different next time. I would have given 5 stars but I felt the price was expensive for what you get.

      I love the vibe of Blueprint! It's in an old automotive repair shop, and still maintains some of that vibe with exposed ductwork and open concept.

      The coffee was amazing, and I like that they're experimenting with things like carbonated coffee and nitro cold brew. The Big Muddy was super creamy and easy to drink, and had simple syrup in it as a sweetener. I would definitely recommend!

    • Mindi A.
      Saint Louis, MO
      57 Coffee reviews
      Jan 10, 2020
      2 photos

      Blueprint has some if the best coffee roasts in STL! And then you go to their shop and get an even better taste of their roasts! I have always loved Blueprint, but did not like driving and parking in the Loop. With their South City location, I get to enjoy their crafted coffees only minutes away.

      This new location is in a converted car shop and they kept the large garage doors. When the weather is nice, they will open them for great air flow. They have a dedicated outdoor space in the back and some tables in front. Their parking lot is very small --3 cars only, but plenty of street parking. They also have a basketball hoop and various balls to play out front.

      Made to order filtered coffee -- ask the barista for their recommendation!

      Dark and Stormy -- cold brew, ginger lime syrup

    • Matthew S.
      Saint Louis, MO
      128
      100
      1169
      Dec 20, 2019
      7 photos

      This is my local coffee spot that always delivers in the clutch. So many great handcrafted drinks here, that I could go on and on about which one to choose on that given day. My go to mainly is the chocolate latte. It's not too sweet, and still has the nice balance of espresso and milk. It's very good.

      Depending on the time of the year, there's also some great small batch coffee to try out. I really liked the Esperanza the last time in.

      They've introduced food at this location since opening and the breakfast tacos hit the spot on a weekend morning. They also serve some pastries from Knead Bakehouse that are really tasty.

      You can't go wrong with what you choose.

      Cheers!
